Oct 25 2009 	A clean and perfectly adequate European-style pension	Don't be frightened by hallways that seem like the setting for &quot;Barton Fink&quot; or a Dashiell Hammett mystery (they're being remodeled). The rooms are perfectly pleasant small pension rooms, nicely decorated with new IKEA furnishings, comfortable new mattresses, and even a microwave/mini-fridge. Baths are down the hall, but newly remodeled and clean with good water pressure. There's free Wi-Fi in the lobby that I had no trouble picking up in my room as well. The location (Kearny at Columbus) is where Chinatown meets Italian North Beach, and the surrounding blocks offer lots of restaurant variety and take-away choices. Happy Donut on the ground floor is very handy for coffee, donuts, croissants, and sandwiches, at any hour. It's an eight-block walk (or $4 taxi ride) from Market Street or BART. Muni buses 9, 20, and 41 are just outside on Columbus, and the frequent 30 and 45 buses are two blocks west on Stockton. I was VERY pleased with the value for the money.	
Jul 6 2009 	Brilliant little gem at a brilliant rate	Originally booked a hostel, but on reading bad reviews, I switched to what was listed on Hostel World as a &quot;Budget Hotel&quot;.On arrival, I was met by a shiny new foyer. The staff, whilst a little brash, were helpful, and always available should we needed them.The upper floors of the hotel however are still being renovated, but certainly has some character to them.Our room (33) overlooked the road, which seemed noisy at first though we quickly adapted to it.There was a TV in the room with a decent selection of channels, and plenty of storage space for 2 peoples clothes. There was additionally a fridge and a microwave.The beds were comfortable and the bedding was changed once during our week stay.Bathrooms were plentiful, and I never queued for one in my time there. The showers seemed very new, and along with the toilets felt like they were cleaned every 15 minutes. Possibly less.The hotel was ideally located for a tourist, as it was about a 20 minute walk down to union square, and about 25 minutes walk to fisherman wharf. Alternately, the 9x bus runs past the hotel regularly, if your feeling lazy.So, if your a student, or on a tight budget, definably consider this hotel.	
