Dec 14 2007 	Best Value in the Area	I stayed at the St. Paul twice for 4 nights each period while I was in between apartment leases. Booked another site for the second time, but was unhappy with it and returned to the St. Paul. The hotel is nothing lavish, but certainly met my needs in terms of basic accomodations and value for the money. You will not find a better place (location, private rooms, etc.) in SF. I rarely saw other guests or the resident crazies that you can get in other budget hotels. Hotel: Basic appointments, relatively small but clean rooms, excellently maintained shower and bath areas, microwave, fridge and TV with many channels, wifi and laundry facilities. Renovations are underway with the lobby, restrooms/showers, and some guest rooms completed. Ask about rooms 18, 27, 28 if you would like a more tranquil spot (not facing the street). These rooms have also been updated.Location: In Northbeach, bordering the Financial district. Bus stop right outside and easy walking distance to whatever you need.Staff: Always more than friendly... thanks to Tommy, Pauline, and the rest! Worked to get me a quiet room with good internet access.	
