Jul 15 2006	Noisy and small but clean and safe	If you're looking for a luxury hotel, you'll need to either pay (a lot) more or stay outside San Francisco. But a room here usually costs just a few dollars more than a dorm bed at the Green Tortoise (hostel) across the street, so it's great if you just want somewhere to rest after a day of sightseeting and a night of partying. (Nothing against Green Tortoise: They're great if you want to meet lots of people.)The location is perfect if you like bars, nightclubs and restaurants: It's right in North Beach, and a few blocks from other attractions such as Chinatown, the Powell Street area and Fisherman's Wharf. It's not so good if you like peace and quiet, as there tend to lots of drunken revellers making lots of noise right until bar closing time (2am), plus noise from traffic.	
